This paper is about multi-hop reasoning in knowledge graphs, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with query answering. Knowledge graphs are a type of database (cs.DB), and the paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it aims to predict target entities.
